Non-league Kidderminster will host Premier League high-flyers West Ham in the fourth round of the FA Cup while Chelsea will play third-tier Plymouth after the draw was made on Sunday. Kidderminster, who play in the sixth tier of English football, shocked Championship side Reading 2-1 in the third round of the competition on Saturday. League One team Plymouth, who beat Birmingham, will travel to face European champions, Chelsea, at Stamford Bridge, while non-league Boreham Wood will visit Bournemouth, who are currently top of the second-tier Championship. Cambridge United’s reward for beating top-flight strugglers Newcastle is a home tie against Championship side Luton. Manchester United or Aston Villa, who meet at Old Trafford on Monday, will play Middlesbrough while Tottenham will face Brighton in an all-Premier League tie. West Ham United’s English striker Jarrod Bowen (R) celebrates with teammates after scoring their late second goal during the English FA Cup third round football match between West Ham United and Leeds United at London Stadium in east London on January 9, 2022. – West Ham won the game 2-0. (Photo by JUSTIN TALLIS / AFP)  The fourth round will be played between February 4 and 7. 